entries.journal_entry_description: Retrieve an experimental Old Republic droid module, a Decentralized Autonomy Chip, that is installed in a battle droid controlled by Borvo the Hutt.
entries.journal_entry_title: Old Republic Droid Modules: Borvo's Battle Droid
entries.task01_journal_entry_description: Borvo is rumored to hang out in the back of a cantina in Moenia. You don't know if this is true, but it couldn't hurt to look.
entries.task02_journal_entry_description: Borvo the Hutt is the best chance of finding this missing droid part. You should speak to him about it.
entries.task03_journal_entry_description: Borvo gave you the location of his vault. You should head there and see if you can break in.
entries.task04_journal_entry_description: There are 8 security codes to override before you can open the vault in the back.
entries.task05_comm_message_text: You've done it! Congratulations. Now all you have to do is make it to the vault and get your precious part.
entries.task06_journal_entry_description: Make your way to the back of the vault and get the droid AI.
entries.task07_journal_entry_description: Make your way back to Borvo and let him know you got your AI from his vault.
entries.task09_comm_message_text: [BEGIN TRANSMISSION]: Please return to the RSF mainframe in Theed. [END TRANSMISSION]
entries.task10_journal_entry_description: Return to Theed and update the RSF mainframe information about acquisition of the Decentralized Autonomy Chip.
entries.task10_journal_entry_title: Return to the RSF Mainframe in Theed
